Standard RNA-seq Analysis Pipeline (Quality Control, Genome Indexing, Mapping and Quantification)
# This is a standardized universal RNA-seq analytical pipeline
# All private server paths are removed for public availability
# Pipeline workflow: Quality control - Genome index construction - Reads mapping - Gene quantification - Result collation

1. Raw Reads Quality Trimming and Filtering
# Create directory for clean sequencing data
mkdir -p 00.clean.data

# Fastp quality control for sample 1 (paired-end reads)
nohup fastp \
-i sample1_R1.fq.gz \
-I sample1_R2.fq.gz \
-o 00.clean.data/sample1_clean_R1.fastq.gz \
-O 00.clean.data/sample1_clean_R2.fastq.gz \
-h fastp_sample1_report.html 

# Fastp quality control for sample 2 (paired-end reads)
nohup fastp \
-i sample2_R1.fq.gz \
-I sample2_R2.fq.gz \
-o 00.clean.data/sample2_clean_R1.fastq.gz \
-O 00.clean.data/sample2_clean_R2.fastq.gz \
-h fastp_sample2_report.html 

2. Reference Genome Index Construction
# Create directory for reference genome files
mkdir -p 01.genome.index

# Convert GFF annotation file to standard GTF format
gffread reference.gff -T -o reference_renamed.gtf

# Extract exon and splice site information for Hisat2 splicing-aware mapping
python extract_exons.py reference_renamed.gtf > exons.txt
python extract_splice_sites.py reference_renamed.gtf > splicesites.txt

# Build splicing-aware reference genome index (multi-threaded)
hisat2-build -f reference.fa \
--ss splicesites.txt \
--exon exons.txt \
-p 7 \
01.genome.index/genome_index

3. Clean Reads Mapping to Reference Genome
# Create directory for mapping results
mkdir -p 02.mapping.results

# Hisat2 paired-end mapping and BAM sorting (sample 1)
hisat2 -p 20 --dta \
-x 01.genome.index/genome_index \
--summary-file 02.mapping.results/sample1_mapping_summary.txt \
-1 00.clean.data/sample1_clean_R1.fastq.gz \
-2 00.clean.data/sample1_clean_R2.fastq.gz \
| samtools sort -@ 10 -o 02.mapping.results/sample1_sorted.bam

# Hisat2 paired-end mapping and BAM sorting (sample 2)
hisat2 -p 20 --dta \
-x 01.genome.index/genome_index \
--summary-file 02.mapping.results/sample2_mapping_summary.txt \
-1 00.clean.data/sample2_clean_R1.fastq.gz \
-2 00.clean.data/sample2_clean_R2.fastq.gz \
| samtools sort -@ 10 -o 02.mapping.results/sample2_sorted.bam

# Hisat2 paired-end mapping and BAM sorting (sample 3)
hisat2 -p 20 --dta \
-x 01.genome.index/genome_index \
--summary-file 02.mapping.results/sample3_mapping_summary.txt \
-1 00.clean.data/sample3_clean_R1.fastq.gz \
-2 00.clean.data/sample3_clean_R2.fastq.gz \
| samtools sort -@ 10 -o 02.mapping.results/sample3_sorted.bam

4. Transcript and Gene Quantification Using StringTie
# Create directory for gene quantification results
mkdir -p 03.quantification.results

# Quantification for sample 1
stringtie -p 30 -e \
-G reference_renamed.gtf \
-o 03.quantification.results/sample1_transcript.gtf \
-A 03.quantification.results/sample1_gene_abundance.tsv \
02.mapping.results/sample1_sorted.bam

# Quantification for sample 2
stringtie -p 30 -e \
-G reference_renamed.gtf \
-o 03.quantification.results/sample2_transcript.gtf \
-A 03.quantification.results/sample2_gene_abundance.tsv \
02.mapping.results/sample2_sorted.bam

# Quantification for sample 3
stringtie -p 30 -e \
-G reference_renamed.gtf \
-o 03.quantification.results/sample3_transcript.gtf \
-A 03.quantification.results/sample3_gene_abundance.tsv \
02.mapping.results/sample3_sorted.bam

5. Expression Matrix Consolidation
# Create final result directory
mkdir -p 04.final.results

# Generate unified gene expression matrix from multiple samples
python prepDE.python2.py -i sample_list.txt
